{
  "doc_id": "47804",
  "text": "During a survey of Proteus mirabilis ␤-lactamases performed in Clermont-Ferrand, France, we observed isolates that exhibited the ␤-lactam resistance phenotype of the IRT/OXA type and produced the same non-TEM ␤-lactamase of pI 6.9 [CITATION_1] . In this study, we report the characterization of this enzyme and its genetic support in 10 clinical P. mirabilis isolates. The 10 nonrepetitive P. mirabilis isolates were collected over 4 years (1996 to 1999) from different patients hospitalized in various wards of the teaching hospital of Clermont-Ferrand, France.",
